cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with breaking an image encryption scheme and identifying security defects in it. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the use of chaotic standard and logistic maps for encryption, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may also be relevant to this category as it deals with the security of a system (image encryption scheme) and identifying vulnerabilities in it. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with an image encryption scheme, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
5. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper may also be relevant to this category as it deals with image encryption and decryption techniques.
